nforming the work of a number of contemporary artists-including Tacita Dean, Jasper Johns, Mary Kelly, Gabriel Orozco, and Gerhard Richter-the concept of the trace is shown to be vital for any account of the aesthetics of trauma; it has left an indelible mark on the history of photography and art as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aPhotographyxSocial aspects. 4aanalogue. 4achance. 4adigitization. 4aexposure. 4aindexicality. 4aphotography. 4atrace. 4atrauma. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226370330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226370330.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles